@NODE "DnLd" "What the heck did I just download?"

 @{b}What the heck did I just download?@{ub}


 @{"MagicWB1.3" LINK "MW13"} is a program which changes OS1.3 from 2 bitplanes (4 colors) to 3
 bitplanes (8 colors) with the MagicWB palette preset so that you can use
 @{"Magic Workbench © by Martin Huttenloher" LINK "MgWB"} on your A500 or A1000!!

 This archive also includes the program @{"PCheck" LINK "PChk"} which allows you to verify the
 current number of bitplanes.  This program can be used for any purpose and not
 just to confirm that MagicWB1.3 is running.

 @{"IconFix1.3" LINK "IF13"} and @{"IconUnfix1.3" LINK "IU13"} are small icon fixing utils which will make your
 icons look like OS2+ icons.

 @{"Template" LINK "Exam"} is just a template pic which I got from another archive and have
 been adding stuff to it as needed.  The template drawer which I added to the
 image has a dotted line around it to show where you need to cut it out for it
 to work properly (cut just @{b}inside@{ub} of the dotted line).

 @{b}system-configuration@{ub} is a pretty nice setup with a really nice mouse pointer
 which you can copy into your devs drawer (make sure you back yours up or rename
 it in case you don't like this one).

 To enhance your MagicWB, look for @{b}MagicWBStuff3.lha@{ub} on aminet in pix/icon!
 This archive by @{"Trevor Morris" LINK "Trev"} contains lots of pix, icons, and imagedrawers to
 go with your MagicWB1.3!

 Also grab up RomIcons1.lha through RomIcons7.lha created by @{"Roman Patzner" LINK "Romn"} on
 any Aminet site in pix/icon for the best looking icons created for @{"MagicWB" LINK "MgWB"}!


 If you are not familiar with @{"MagicWB" LINK "MgWB"}, see the included @{"Example.pic" LINK "Exam"}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Inst" "How do I get these goodies running?"

 @{b}How do I get these goodies running?@{ub}


 @{"MagicWB1.3" LINK "MW13"}
 @{"PCheck" LINK "PChk"}
 @{"IconFix1.3" LINK "IF13"}
 @{"IconUnfix1.3" LINK "IU13"}
 @{"Example.pic & Template.pic" LINK "Exam"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "MW13" "How do I get MagicWB1.3 running?"
@TOC "Inst"

 @{fg shine}MagicWB1.3@{fg text}


 Couldn't be simpler: just insert this command @{b}after@{ub} the LOADWB command and @{b}before@{ub}
 the ENDCLI command in your startup-sequence.  Now reboot the machine and
 presto!

 For example:

 C:BlahBlah
 .
 .
 .
 LoadWB
 C:MagicWB1.3
 EndCLI
@ENDNODE

@NODE "PChk" "How do I get PCheck running?"
@TOC "Inst"

 @{fg shine}PCheck@{fg text}


 This one is even simpler: just open a CLI and type the command!  That is it,
 and PCheck will return the current screen name and tell you how many bitplanes
 it is using.

 For example:

 9.@{fg shine}System1.3:@{fg text}> df0:c/pcheck
 @{b}Workbench has 3 bitplanes@{ub}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Exam" "What do I do with the Pictures?"
@TOC "Inst"

 @{fg shine}Example.pic@{fg text}


 @{b}Example.pic@{ub} is just a snapshot of @{"my" LINK "Trev"} WorkBench. You may show it
 with your favorite viewer, or load it into DPaint.


 @{fg shine}Template.pic@{fg text}


 The @{b}Template.pic@{ub} is for making your own icons (use it in DPaint). Or,
 you could download some VERY NICE premade ones by @{"Trevor Morris" LINK "Trev"} and
 @{"Roman Patzner" LINK "Romn"}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "IF13" "How do I get IconFix1.3 running?"
@TOC "Inst"

 @{fg shine}IconFix1.3@{fg text}


 Since OS2+ automatically adds a bevel to each icon, the ones you make using
 the template will still look strange, as will the ones you download from
 @{"Trevor Morris" LINK "Trev"} and @{"Roman Patzner" LINK "Romn"}...so you need @{b}IconFix1.3@{ub} and @{"IconUnfix1.3" LINK "IU13"}!

 IconFix1.3 will add the extra bevel to your icons for you automatically!!  All
 you have to do is specify the icon's name @{b}WITHOUT the ".info"@{ub}

 For example:

 10.@{fg shine}System1.3:@{fg text}> c:iconfix1.3 df0:utils/SID

 This will add the bevelled edge to the SID icon "@{b}SID.info@{ub}"
@ENDNODE

@NODE "IU13" "How do I get IconUnfix1.3 running?"
@TOC "Inst"

 @{fg shine}IconUnfix1.3@{fg text}


 IconUnfix1.3 is just the opposite of @{"IconFix1.3" LINK "IF13"}, meaning that it will remove
 the extra bevel on your icons (ie it will reverse the effects of @{"IconFix1.3" LINK "IF13"})
 Just specify the icon's name @{b}WITHOUT the ".info"@{ub}

 For example:

 11.@{fg shine}System1.3:@{fg text}> c:iconunfix1.3 df0:utils/SID

 This will remove the bevelled edge from the SID icon "@{b}SID.info@{ub}"
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Make" "What did you use to make all this stuff?"

 @{b}What did you use to make all this stuff?@{ub}


 The enclosed programs were coded by @{"Cléo Saulnier" LINK "Cntc"} using SAS/C® 6.51 on a
 A3000/030 wih 14M RAM under OS3.0. Or, sometimes on a 10M A4000/040 under
 OS3.1...so hopefully this works on everything (even though it's probably only
 useful for those of you with a A500 or A1000).

 The graphics and this guide file were done by @{"Trevor Morris" LINK "Trev"} on the same
 A3000 using OpalVision, Art Department Professional and Deluxe Paint.
@ENDNODE

